commit.message:
Version 0.2.3

Add a workaround for the vim bug described in https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/vim_dev/1M7UMk-E1to

Version 0.2.2

Added frawor-od-override [1][1] http://vimpluginloader.sourceforge.net/doc/frawor.txt.html#frawor-od-override

Version 0.2.1

Made loading of command dictionary functions (it and completion) more lazyAdded “usedictcompsplitfunc” command option

Version 0.2

Removed double loading functionality. It is assumed now that you split files into plugin/ with interface and autoload/ with everything elseMoved almost everything from plugin/ to autoload/Improved @/python: it now supports case “both pythons are present”. Python3 modules are loaded from python3/, python2 from python/; removed s:_r.py resourceMade @/signs and @/commands features not be ignoredeps onesAdded function autoloading support: "function" key value may be 3-tuple [{plid}, {plver}, {funcname}], {funcname} is pulled from s:_aufunctions dictionary
Version 0.1.24: Added some code minimization possibilities to @/fwc/constructor

Version 0.1.23

@/fwc/constructor refactoring and documenting: it can now be used outside of FWC@/fwc/*: Added support for numbers in place of variables: now “1” no longer refers to “s:1”
Version 0.1.22: Optimization and minor bug fixes
Version 0.1.21: Added require core featureAdded s:_loading variable

Version 0.1.20

Added os.readsystem() functionMade os.run also accept plain strings as the first

Version 0.1.19

Made plugin/frawor/base64 use built-in and() and or() functions if they are availableRefactored plugin/frawor/fwc/constructor
Version 0.1.18: Fixed FraworLoad({expandable_plid})
Version 0.1.16: Fixed os.path.abspath and os.path.exists under windows

Version 0.1.15

Made `isfunc' be also a filterLarge perfomance improvements, fixed plugin reloadingVarious completion fixes
Version 0.1.14: Fixed behavior of the plugin when &wildignore is "*"

Version 0.1.13

Various compatibility improvements (now works on vim-7.2.242)@/decorators/altervars: Added `folds' special setter@/fwc: Made `range' check be aware of -onlystrings option, various fixes
Version 0.1.11: @/os: Made relpath be aware of paths with trailing path separators

Version 0.1.10

@/os: Added os.path.relpath function      Made abspath also work for paths like a/b/c where a/ does not exist      Made os.path.normpath also simplify its argument

Version 0.1.9

@/os: Added os.path.relpath function      Made abspath also work for paths like a/b/c where a/ does not exist      Made os.path.normpath also simplify its argument

Version 0.1.8

Improved `path pipe and completion\nMade unmap handle «... does not exist» error

Version 0.1.7

@/table: Improved stdisplaywidth emulation@/fwc/compiler: Fixed `cur arguments inside {optional} section
Version 0.1.6: Fixed completion and checker for +history altervars special

Version 0.1.5

@/fwc changes:- Added `idof check\n- Fixed `either' key: checks in alternatives were effectively ignored
Version 0.1.4: Added @/history module

Version 0.1.3

@/mappings: Added possibility to specify functions in `strfunc and `func' keys (required for plugin autoloading)\n@/table: Posted strdisplaywidth function (relevant for old vims, for newer ones it is just a reference to built-in strdisplaywidth)
Version 0.1: Initial upload
